I have a persona page in Angular with a static green 
circle icon. Replace it with a Pioneer-style floating 
circular button with a rotating outer ring. This component 
appears on all persona views (Associate, Manager, HR Partner).

No external libraries. Complete implementation. No stubs.

════════════════════════════════════════
COMPONENT: FloatingPersonaButtonComponent
selector: app-floating-persona-btn
════════════════════════════════════════

This is a standalone component placed in app.component.html
so it persists across persona route changes.
It is ONLY visible on persona routes — hidden on 
landing and ecosystem pages.

Show it when route includes '/persona' or '/lens'.
Hide it on '/' and '/ecosystem'.

In app.component.ts:
  import { Router, NavigationEnd } from '@angular/router';

  showPersonaBtn = false;

  constructor(private router: Router) {
    this.router.events.subscribe(event => {
      if (event instanceof NavigationEnd) {
        this.showPersonaBtn = 
          event.url.includes('/persona') || 
          event.url.includes('/lens');
      }
    });
  }

In app.component.html:
  <app-floating-persona-btn 
    *ngIf="showPersonaBtn">
  </app-floating-persona-btn>

