RULES
════════════════════════════════════════

1. The SVG rings use transform-origin: 60px 60px 
   (the center of the 120×120 viewBox). Do NOT use 
   transform-origin: center — SVG and CSS centers 
   differ and the ring will orbit off-center.

2. Two rings rotating in opposite directions at 
   different speeds (12s CW, 20s CCW) — this creates 
   the organic non-mechanical feel. Do not make them 
   the same speed or direction.

3. stroke-dasharray on .rotating-ring uses uneven 
   segments deliberately — "30 10 8 10 5 10 15 10 20 10"
   The irregular pattern makes it feel like a 
   scientific instrument, not a loading spinner.

4. .persona-menu transforms from bottom right — 
   transform-origin: bottom right — so it unfolds 
   toward the content, not away from it.

5. $event.stopPropagation() on menu-item click is 
   mandatory — without it the click bubbles to 
   .persona-float and immediately closes the menu 
   that was just interacted with.

6. menu-backdrop uses z-index: -1 relative to 
   :host's stacking context — it catches clicks 
   outside the menu without needing a full-screen 
   overlay that blocks page interaction.

7. Do NOT add transition to animation-duration — 
   CSS cannot transition animation-duration. The 
   speed change on hover is instant, which actually 
   feels more responsive than a transition would.

